# This working tree is shared between the Windows host and the Linux
# devcontainer. Without a fixed policy, Windows git (autocrlf=true) writes
# CRLF to disk while container git expects LF, and every touched file shows
# as "modified" inside the container. Pinning LF for all text files makes
# both sides agree. Rust, Cargo, and VS Code on Windows all handle LF fine.
* text=auto eol=lf
